name: Tumbledown Mountain

current_conditions.ai_summary: Maine's favorite playground hike, featuring a chimney scramble ('Fat Man's Misery') and a pristine alpine pond for swimming.

generated_description:
The Experience

Tumbledown is arguably the most fun hike in the state. You crawl through a granite fissure known as Fat Man's Misery to emerge at an alpine tarn perfect for a mid-hike swim.

The Challenge

The Loop Trail requires scrambling and squeezing through tight rocks. It is physically demanding and requires using your hands.

Local Insight

If you have a large backpack or dog, avoid the Loop Trail chimney; take the Brook Trail out-and-back instead.

trails_config.name: Loop and Brook Trail
trails_config.description: Ascend the steep Loop trail through the chimney and descend the gradual Brook trail.
